<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../layouts/head', { title: title, seo: typeof seo !== 'undefined' ? seo : null }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/static-pages.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../layouts/nav') %>

  <main class="static-page">
    <div class="static-wrap">
      <header class="static-hero">
        <h1>Contact HelloRun</h1>
        <p>Reach the HelloRun team for runner support, organizer inquiries, payment concerns, data requests, and community event questions.</p>
      </header>

      <% if (source === 'organizer-dashboard') { %>
        <section class="static-card">
          <h2>Organizer Support</h2>
          <p>For organizer support, include your application ID, event name, or event reference code.</p>
        </section>
      <% } %>

      <section class="static-grid">
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>General Support</h2>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hellorunonline@gmail.com">hellorunonline@gmail.com</a></p>
          <p>HelloRun is operated from Benguet, Philippines, with support handled online for runners and organizers joining from different locations.</p>
          <p>Typical response time: 24-48 hours. Complex registration, payment, or proof review concerns may take longer if they require organizer confirmation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Runner Support</h2>
          <p>Contact us if you cannot access your account, need help finding an event, have questions about registration status, or need guidance on submitting run proof.</p>
          <p>When writing about a registration, include your event name, confirmation code, and the email address used on your HelloRun account.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="static-grid">
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Organizer Inquiries</h2>
          <p>Organizers can contact HelloRun about event setup, application status, participant management, proof review, payment receipt review, leaderboards, and certificates.</p>
          <p>Include your application ID, event name, or event reference code when available so the support team can find the correct record.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Payment or Registration Concerns</h2>
          <p>For paid events, payment receipts are reviewed based on the event configuration and organizer workflow. Send only the information needed to identify the registration and explain the concern.</p>
          <p>HelloRun support can help route platform issues, while event-specific refund, package, or approval decisions may still depend on the event organizer's published rules.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="static-grid">
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Data and Privacy Requests</h2>
          <p>Use the support email for privacy questions, correction requests, account data concerns, or questions about uploaded proof handling.</p>
          <p>Before sending screenshots or personal records by email, describe the issue first so the team can confirm what information is actually needed.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Event Partnerships</h2>
          <p>Schools, running groups, local communities, and event organizers can contact HelloRun about using the platform for virtual, on-site, or hybrid running events.</p>
          <p>Helpful details include your organization name, event type, expected dates, distances, payment setup, and whether you need proof review, leaderboard, or certificate support.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="static-card">
        <h2>Before You Contact Us</h2>
        <p>Check the <a href="/faq">FAQ</a> and <a href="/how-it-works">How It Works</a> pages first for common account, registration, payment receipt, and run result review questions.</p>
        <p>Important policy links: <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, <a href="/terms">Terms and Conditions</a>, <a href="/data-usage-policy">Data Usage Policy</a>, and <a href="/refund-and-cancellation-policy">Refund and Cancellation Policy</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../layouts/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  <script>if (window.lucide) lucide.createIcons();</script>
</body>
</html>
